Program: Letter from America by Alistair Cooke
Title: Judge Zobel and the Louise Woodward verdict
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00yj9wg
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 14 Nov 1997
The verdict in the Louise Woodward trial, the ability of Judge Zobel to reduce the severity of the conviction, and the difference between state and federal law in the US.